1. MONITOR LIVE PROCESSES
top → real-time process monitoring
ps aux → list of all running processes

2. CAPTURE RAM ( MEMORY DUMP )
sudo dd if=/dev/mem of=ram_dump.mem bs=1M
sudo insmod lime.ko "path=/home/user/memdump.lime format=lime"

3. TCP/UDP PACKETS
Capture a file - sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -w capture.pcap
Show only TCP - sudo tcpdump tcp
Show only UDP - sudo tcpdump udp

4. MONITOR HARD DISK
Disk usage - df -h
I/O operations - iostat
Disk read/write in real time - iotop

5. MONITOR VIRTUAL MEMORY
using vmstat - vmstat 1
swap memory - free -h
check memory usage per process - top

6. MONITOR CACHE MEMORY
cache memory - free -h
